It's understood the provincial executive committee has resolved to fire eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede. DURBAN - The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal is mum on the future of embattled eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede. It's understood the provincial executive committee has resolved to fire her. READ: Gumede to be fired as eThekwini mayor According to sources, the municipality is also in for a major shake-up. Sources have told eNCA that the entire executive committee must vacate their positions. The ANC has not yet confirmed this. READ: KZN ANC mum on Gumede's fate The party said it will communicate its resolution at a briefing on Tuesday. KZN ANC spokesperson Ricardo Mthembu on Monday said the meeting has been concluded. "We're dealing with so many issues. We're not going to comment until Tuesday." The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal is mum on the future of embattled eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede.